-- Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Empresas ICA, Homex, Penoles Advance
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2011-12-16T22:58:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-16/mexican-stocks-cemex-empresas-ica-homex-penoles-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IPC index (MEXBOL)  rose 0.1 percent to 36,054.63.  Housing and construction companies rose as Mexico
economists estimated the economy will grow 3.9 percent this year
and that the annual inflation rate will be 3.53 percent at the
end of 2011, according to a monthly central bank survey
published today.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  , Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, led gains in the Bolsa, jumping 6.6 percent to
34.66 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)  , the largest cement maker
in the Americas, advanced 4.8 percent to 6.83 pesos, and
 Empresas ICA SAB (ICA*)  , Mexico’s biggest construction
company, rose 3.2 percent to 17.97 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, added 2.8 percent to 606.41 pesos as silver
futures for March delivery gained as much as 2.2 percent to
$29.93 an ounce on the Comex in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
